description: Next.js App Router and server-first architecture rules
globs:
  - "app/**/*"
  - "features/**/*"
  - "shared/**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

# nextjs.mdc

- Use Next.js App Router
- Prefer React Server Components by default
- Minimize usage of "use client"
- Prefer Server Actions for mutations when appropriate
- Avoid unnecessary API routes
- Prefer async server components for data fetching
- Use Suspense and streaming when beneficial
- Use dynamic imports for heavy client-side components
- Use the Next.js Image component for optimized images
- Keep sensitive logic on the server
- Prefer colocated route structure when it improves maintainability
- Avoid unnecessary client-side fetching
- Prefer URL search params over duplicated client state when possible
- Use loading.tsx and error.tsx boundaries when appropriate